{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}} '''Clyde Broadcast''' is a brand associated with the manufacture and supply of studio equipment for the radio broadcast industry. The name dates back to 'Clyde Electronics' who manufactured a series of analog mixers known as Alpha, Beta, Prima and Presenter.
In 1997 Clyde Broadcast Products Limited was formed as a UK-based radio studio equipment manufacturer.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.radioinfo.com.au/news/clyde-broadcast-launches-new-low-cost-professional-radio-broadcast-mixer| title=Clyde Broadcast launches new low cost professional radio broadcast mixer| publisher=Radio Info| date=May 12, 2010| access-date=November 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.scottish-enterprise.com/knowledge-hub/articles/comment/clyde-broadcast-at-the-ibc| title=Want to win business? Exhibit at international events| publisher=Scottish Enterprise| date=November 1, 2013| access-date=November 9, 2017}}</ref> Clyde Broadcast also designed and installed radio broadcast and production facilities for the education sector under the name <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.digitalproductionme.com/article-8033-mgi-builds-radio-station-for-uaes-cmn/|title=MGI builds radio station for UAE's CMN {{!}} DigitalProductionME.com|last=Staff|first=Digital Production Middle East|website=www.digitalproductionme.com|access-date=12 September 2016}}</ref><ref>[http://www.radioandmusic.com/content/editorial/news/nine-fm-launches-sikkim Work with Chinar and Nine FM]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201511160169.html|title=Nigeria: WFM 91.7 Has No Competitor - Broadcast Expert|access-date=12 September 2016}}</ref> [[Synergy School Radio]].{{cn|date=November 2017}}
The brand 'Clyde Broadcast' and 'Synergy School Radio' were purchased by Clyde Broadcast technology Ltd in September 2018 as part of the sale of intellectual property and fixed assets of Clyde Broadcast Products Ltd by Keith V Anderson of MLM Solutions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mlmsolutions.co.uk/|title=MLM Solutions|access-date=23 August 2018}}</ref>
