'''LPA512''' ([[Serbian language|Serbian]] ЛПА512) was an industrial [[programmable logic controller]] - a small (438 * 286 * 278 mm ), portable, [[computer]] developed by [[Ivo Lola Ribar Institute]] of [[Serbia]] in 1986 as an enhancement to its prior product, [[PA512]]. It was first deployed in [[Tovarna avtomobilov Maribor|Maribor car factory]].

